🧭 CORE USER FLOW (MANDATORY)

1. Select Namespace (dropdown)
2. Select Deployment (filtered dropdown)
3. Select Pod (filtered dropdown)
4. Select Tail Size:
   - 100 / 200 / 500 / 1000 / 5000
5. Click “Load Logs”

---

🧠 DATA FETCHING MODEL (CRITICAL)

🔴 NO LIVE STREAMING ("-f") by default

The system MUST NOT stream logs continuously.

---

🟢 Initial Load (Snapshot)

Fetch logs using:

oc logs <pod> --tail=<N>

Then:

- Render logs in UI
- Store the timestamp of the last log line as "lastSeenTimestamp"

---

🟡 Refresh Mechanism (CRITICAL FEATURE)

On user clicking “Refresh”:

Fetch ONLY new logs using:

oc logs <pod> --since-time=<lastSeenTimestamp>

---

🔵 Merge Behavior

- Append new logs to existing logs
- Remove duplicates (if last log overlaps)
- Keep full chronological order

---

🟣 Retention Rule

- Keep only the last N logs (based on selected tail size)
- Older logs are discarded from UI only (not modified at source)

---

